# List Manager Module Context

## Goal

Build a reusable list manager where users can add individual items and apply preset bundles that expand into multiple items.

## Core Use Cases

- Grocery: add one dish preset that expands to related ingredients.
  - Example "Spaghetti Night": spaghetti noodles, tomato sauce, vegetables.
- Vacation planning: add activity-duration presets that expand to multiple day entries.
  - Example: 5 hiking days, 3 skiing days, 6 vacation days.

## Product Rules

- Users can add, edit, remove, and reorder individual list items.
- Presets are templates that expand into concrete items at insert time.
- Expanded items should remain editable after insertion.
- The source preset should be traceable in metadata for analytics and audit.
- Users can mix manual items and preset-generated items in the same list.

## Data Modeling Guidance

- Keep presets and list items as separate concepts.
- Prefer stable IDs for presets and generated items.
- Store enough metadata to regenerate, diff, or explain inserted bundles.
- Avoid tight coupling to one domain so grocery and travel both fit.

## Near-Term Scope

- Start with simple lists, manual item entry, and preset expansion.
- Add quantity and duration fields where useful.
- Keep collaboration and real-time syncing out of first iteration.
